photos.name: The Wanderer
photos.description:
Canon 6d Tamron 15-30mm F2.8 at F3.2 15mm ISO 6400 25s. Single image - no compositing or exposure blending and not even my usual panorama.

From my previous image - Finding my way again - I went back to the dunes. I arrived before it got dark this time and managed to do an amount of scouting for compositions. Armed with visibility and a GPS I worked out a number of suitable locations and used photopills (app) to help with some of the visualisation.

I prefer crescent moon lighting, but if I don't have that - I will build the light. I was experimenting with a new setup this time. Will blog about it soon in more detail.

photos.name: Brooklyn Cove Panorama
photos.description:
This is a panoramic view of the little cove in the middle of Brooklyn Bridge Park.. This location has a beautiful view of the city and is framed by the Brooklyn and Manhattan Bridges. Always wanted to try this full panorama. Ended up getting kicked off the rocks just before sunset, but fortunately, I was able to sneak back on during blue hour and snap some shots.

This ended up being a six-image stitch at about 60 second exposure times. Took some liberties scaling the final stitch to a format I liked, and also the reflection was enhanced in post.

photos.name: Path of Awakening
photos.description:
Concerns about 500px
1.One of my images recently was labeled as adult content, probably only because of the title which said :

, about a forest warming up in the sun. 500px replied it's was not because of them, so what robot is?? 
2. Today I discovered an increase of 1200 followers in day?? Normally I get an email when someone starts following me, but nope, not this time. The moment I posted an new image today, it stopped. Something is not right here!
3. The I kiss your ass, you kiss mine policy seems to work well on 500px. Some people apparently have all day to do this.
4. I see lots of good images that never reach the higher ranks, such a shame
5. I think I got the meaning of 500px, its 500 x P , the p standing for patagonia or play boy model,......:-) although beautiful, too much is too much
